@*
    CcHelpHint — a tiny inline (?) affordance for a non-obvious field/concept.

    One plain-language sentence in a native HTML title tooltip (no JS, no popper,
    survives a strict CSP). Drop it right after a <label> so an IDM / ARS operator
    can hover the concept where it first appears:

      <label class="form-label fw-semibold">Base DN <CcHelpHint Text="..." /></label>

    Deliberately attribute-string only (no child content, no interpolation) so it
    is safe to sprinkle into the big Sync pages without tripping the Razor source
    generator.
*@

<span class="cc-help-hint" tabindex="0" role="img" aria-label="@Text" title="@Text">
    <i class="fas fa-circle-question"></i>
</span>

@code {
    /// <summary>The one-sentence plain-language explanation shown on hover/focus.</summary>
    [Parameter, EditorRequired] public string Text { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}
